On Mon, 3 May 1999, Richard A Nelson wrote:
> I've a 2.2.7 kernel, used for multiple systems, and its working fine -
> except for an IBM PS/2 9595 (MCA) all SCSI box.
> 
> On the 9595 box (with the newest MCA scsi drivers 3.1e), SCSI only
> (IBM Fast SCSI-2 Adapter), I'm getting errors that the MCA SCSI
> code can't obtain IRQ 14...  Bummer, I need IDE devices for some
> of the other boxen ;-{ 
> 
> I read ide.txt and then used the following in lilo.conf (on one line):
> append="mca-pentium,ibmmcascsi=display,0x3540,7,
>         hda=none,hdb=none,hdc=none,hdd=none,ide0=noprobe,ide1=noprobe"
"ide0=noprobe,ide1=noprobe" this will by default do
"hda=none,hdb=none,hdc=none,hdd=none"
By calling the later is saying the interface is okay but skip the drives.
The form wil skip the interface.
Did this long append work in 2.2.6?
> 
> However, I still see the errors from hd{a,b} and ide0!
> 
> Have I missunderstood ide.txt?
